Class G4JWebSocketClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.java_websocket.WebSocketAdapter
      • org.java_websocket.AbstractWebSocket
        • org.java_websocket.client.WebSocketClient
          • vip.floatationdevice.guilded4j.G4JWebSocketClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable, org.java_websocket.WebSocket, org.java_websocket.WebSocketListener

    public class G4JWebSocketClient
extends org.java_websocket.client.WebSocketClient
    Guilded4J WebSocket event manager, built in by G4JClient, also can be used independently.

    NOTE:

    - After creating G4JWebSocketClient object you need to manually call connect(), close() or reconnect() to start/stop receiving WebSocket events.
